cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with predicting signed links in social networks and proposes a model that explores user personality via social media data.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a novel signed link prediction model.
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper uses psychology theories to obtain personality information and investigates its role in signed link prediction.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a model for signed link prediction and evaluates its effectiveness on real-world datasets.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category as the paper deals with natural language data from social media to extract personality information.
